caption.text: (taken today) Warning: I'm gonna go off a bit about self-portraits. You've been warned. I'm at work, but I don't want to be. But I'm watching computer do their thing, and basically babysitting, so I have time to write this. I see a lot of talk on IG (and other places) about self-portraits. I read that the people who take pictures of themselves must want to simply see their face all the time. Or that they're in love with themselves. Or that their self-absorbed. All that and more. Let me just say this first. I used to think some of that too. When I first got on Flickr in 2008 I saw people who did 365s and wondered why they liked themselves so much. I also saw those who put up the occasional self-portrait - or even a couple a week. It didn't make sense to me, and I wanted none of it. My landscapes were much more fun to look at than my mug. I went for a very long time feeling this way. I would put up a picture of myself - half hidden or something - every now and then, just so people would know that I was real. But as you look through my pictures here on IG now, you'll see that I post quite a few self-portraits. It's not because I'm in love with myself, that there's nothing better to shoot, or even that I want to see my face. Self-portraits are *still* the most difficult shot to take, and absolutely the most difficult to upload for the world to see. But I do it anyway, and I encourage others to do the #7daysofsps and post pictures of themselves. Why do I do it? For many reasons, really. First - I'm always available to me. If I need practice shooting portraits, I'm easy to find. Next - I know that if I can pull off a portrait of myself that I actually think is ok, I know that I can do the same for someone else. I'm my biggest and worst critic. Last - it's my therapy. Just over a year ago I was encouraged by a very good friend to do self-portraits, and to continue to do them. I didn't want to, but did it anyway. It is therapeutic. It's calming. It helps me focus. It reminds me that I'm ok, and forces me to show myself to the world instead of hiding behind the camera. What I'm saying is that I'm going to continue to post SPs. I post them for me. If you want to look at them, please do. If you don't want to, that's ok too. First and foremost I'm here for photography. I'm here to learn and share. Thanks for listening. If you'd like to unfollow me now, the button is above. :) #sumsion
